physical_appearance: These are two identical pages of a publication. One is more well worn than the other. This is from the periodical 'The Orient Illustrated Weekly' published on 3 February 1946. The title is printed on the left, and includes four black-and-white photographs with a short caption at the bottom of the page. The photographs are taken on the occasion of the 50th birthday celebrations of Netaji Subhas Chandra Bose, depicting the procession through the streets of Calcutta. The edges of the page are slightly torn.
